{
  "text": "I don't mean to be covering ground that we've already covered, but there're some points that we have trouble with fully understanding and sometimes I have to ask the question a different way to fully understand it. Thank you. So at the start of this 75, 000-year cycle we know that the quarantine was set up. I am assuming then that the Guardians were aware of the infringements on free will that would occur if they didn't set this up at that time and therefore did it. This— Is this correct? I am Ra. This is partially incorrect. The incorrectness is as follows: those entities whose third-density experience upon your Red Planet was brought to a close prematurely were aided genetically while being transferred to this third density. This, although done in a desire to aid, was seen as infringement upon free will. The light quarantine which consists of the Guardians, or gardeners as you may call them, which would have been in effect thus was intensified.",
